==Japanese==
=== Etymology ===
{{ja-kanjitab-top}}
! [[日]] || [[曜]]
{{ja-kanjitab-bottom}}
From Latin ''[[dies solis]]'' ("sun's day") through Indian astrology in the fifth century as Sanskrit ''ravidina'' (''ravi'', "sun") into Buddhist astrology in the 8th century as 日曜日: [[日]] (にち, ''nichi'', "sun") + [[曜日]] (ようび, ''yōbi'', "day of the week").

===Noun===
{{janoun|にちようび|nichiyőbi}}
# [[Sunday]]
===Synonyms===
*[[日曜]] -- Note: this pair of [[wikipedia:Kanji|Kanji]] is just a shortened way of writing 日曜日; both 日曜日 and 日曜 have the same [[wikipedia:pronunciation|pronunciation]]

[[Category:ja:Days of the week|にちようび]]

